main event: LT ADAMS at Lincoln AFB observed a fast-moving object at a 30° elevation and 5 seconds duration on 19 SEP 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed at a high rate of speed; it was small in size; the observation was affected by distortion due to the object's speed; the azimuth of the object was approximately 030°; the object was sighted while LT ADAMS was on alert duty in an observation tower.
